article.headline: Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 78, Texas-San Antonio 63
article.story: SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- Chris Daniels scored 18 points and grabbed seven rebounds to help lead Texas A&M-Corpus Christi to a 78-63 victory over Texas-San Antonio on Saturday night. Cedric Smith came off the bench to add 17 points, and Scooby Johnson had 14 points and a team-high nine rebounds. The Islanders (15-4, 6-0 Southland) led 34-23 at the break and took a 17-point lead with 3:01 remaining in the game. They hit 52 percent from the floor and never trailed. Melvin Smith led the Roadrunners (5-14, 1-5) with 18 points and six rebounds. Andrew Francis and Isaiah Allen each added 17 points. Allen hit three 3-pointers and made all eight of his free-throw attempts.
